election_record.label: Connecticut 1824 Electoral College

overview.note: Walter B. Kibber, Frederick Wolcott, James Hillhouse and David Daggett are listed as electors in the Original Election Returns but no votes are listed for them. They may have been Federalist electors. Timothy Pitkin, Calvin Goddard and Roger M. Sherman are also listed as electors in the Original Election Returns with no votes listed. They, however, all received votes as part of the Federalist ticket in Farmington, the only town for which the scattering votes are available by candidate.

sub_unit.name: Sherman
sub_unit.note: "Those from Sherman came too late." Middlesex Gazette (Middletown, CT). December 1, 1824.

sub_unit.name: Granby
sub_unit.note: Moses Warren received 62 votes as Moses Warner.

sub_unit.name: Saybrook
sub_unit.note: "The votes from Saybrook were not returned." Middlesex Gazette (Middletown, CT). December 1, 1824.

sub_unit.name: Oxford
sub_unit.note: "Those from Oxford were rejected for want of a seal." Middlesex Gazette (Middletown, CT). December 1, 1824.
